# Git attributes — LC Base Template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Normalize line endings repo-wide so the codebase stays LF-only, no matter
# which OS a contributor is on. Pairs with Prettier's `endOfLine: "lf"`:
# Prettier *checks* for LF, git *enforces* it on checkout/commit. Without this,
# a Windows clone (default CRLF) could reintroduce noisy line-ending diffs.
#
# `text=auto` lets git auto-detect text vs binary files.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Bun's lockfile is machine-generated — collapse it in diffs / PR reviews to
# cut noise, and mark it generated so GitHub's language stats ignore it.
bun.lock -diff linguist-generated=true
